<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629452>
    dc:description "Fig. 47. Georeferenced collection records of Lasioglossum (D.) perparvum (Ellis, 1914) (black squares) and predicted distribution by maximum entropy ecological niche modelling in Maxent (colour shading). Warmer colours indicate higher cloglog probability of occurrence." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629452/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629514>
    dc:description "Fig. 76. Male genitalia illustrated in dorsal view and positioned such that the gonostylus is parallel to the plane of vision. Retrorse lobes are also illustrated separately to the bottom left of each figure in lateral view, positioned parallel to the plane of vision. A. Lasioglossum (D.) angelicum sp. nov.B. L. (D.) coactus (Cresson, 1872). C. L. (D.) deludens sp. nov. D. L. (D.) diabolicum sp. nov.E. L. (D.) gaudiale (Sandhouse, 1924). F. L. (D.) gloriosum sp. nov. (the retrorse lobe was not visible for illustration). G. L. (D.) helianthi (Cockerell, 1916). H. L. (D.) holzenthali sp. nov. I. L. (D.) indagator sp. nov. J. L. (D.) magnitegula sp. nov. K. L. (D.) perparvum (Ellis, 1914). L. L. (D.) profoundum sp. nov. M. L. (D.) pseudotegulare (Cockerell, 1896). N. L. (D.) rufodeludens sp. nov. This genital capsule was damaged during dissection and some details may be slightly distorted.O. L. (D.) stictaspis (Sandhouse, 1923) (holotype) (reproduced from Gardner & Gibbs 2022). P. L. (D.) tegulariforme (Crawford, 1907) (reproduced from Gardner & Gibbs 2022). Scale bars = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629514/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629518>
    dc:description "Fig. 78. Mesoscutum pubescence. A. Lasioglossum perparvum (Ellis, 1914), ♀, lateral view, with pubescence very short and sparse. B. L. magnitegula sp. nov., ♀, dorsal view, with pubescence very short and sparse. C. L. angelicum sp. nov., ♀, lateral view, with pubescence long and dense. D. L. deludens sp. nov., ♀, dorsal view, with pubescence long and dense. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629518/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629520>
    dc:description "Fig. 79. Tegulae.A. Lasioglossum perparvum (Ellis, 1914), ♀, sparsely punctate, not exceeding posterior margin of mesoscutum, and inner posterior margin straight. B. L. magnitegula sp. nov., ♀, densely punctate, exceeding posterior margin of mesoscutum, and inner posterior margin concave. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629520/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629522>
    dc:description "Fig. 80. T1–T2 apical rims. A. Lasioglossum perparvum (Ellis, 1914), ♀, apical rims with some fine punctures and short setae (arrow). B. L. magnitegula sp. nov., ♀, apical rims impunctate and glabrous. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629522/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629598>
    dc:description "Fig. 115. Tegulae. A. Lasioglossum helianthi (Cockerell, 1916), ♂, inner posterior margin concave with distinct posterior projection (outline on left). B. L. perparvum (Ellis, 1914), ♂, inner posterior margin nearly straight without posterior projection (outline on left). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7629600>
    dc:description "Fig. 116. T1–T2.A. Lasioglossum holzenthalisp. nov., ♂, with apical rims mostly punctate. B. L. perparvum (Ellis, 1914), ♂, with apical rims punctate only on basal margin. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7629600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

